Following the death of ANC stalwart Winnie Madikizela-Mandela, President Cyril Ramaphosa, Gauteng Premier David Makhura and members of the ANC gathered at the former first lady’s home in Soweto to celebrate her illustrious contributions to the South African political sphere. Addressing the media outside Madikizela-Mandela’s home, Ramaphosa announced that Madikizela-Mandela would receive a national official funeral to be held on April 14 and an official memorial service would be held on April 11 at the Orlando Stadium in Soweto. Madikizela-Mandela died at Milpark hospital on Monday after a long illness. She was 81.   